{"title_page": "Dutch Caribbean", "text_new": "{{short description|Parts of the Kingdom of the Netherlands located in the Caribbean}}\n{{For|the integral territories of the constituent country of the Netherlands|Caribbean Netherlands}}\n{{Infobox| bodyclass = geography\n| title     = Dutch Caribbean\n| image     = [[File:Flag of the Netherlands.svg|225px]]\n| caption   = [[Flag of the Netherlands|Flag of the Kingdom of the Netherlands]]\n| image2    = [[File:Dutch Caribbean location map.svg|250px]]\n| caption2  = Location of the Dutch Caribbean islands\n<div style=\"text-align:left\">\n{{legend|#FF7F00|[[Aruba]]}}\n{{legend|#0086CB|[[Cura\u00e7ao]]}}\n{{legend|#EF001A|[[Sint Maarten]]}}\n{{legend|#328925|[[Caribbean Netherlands]] <small>(from west to east)</small>:\n:*[[Bonaire]]\n:*[[Saba]]\n:*[[Sint Eustatius]]}}\n</div>\n| label1    = Area\n| data1     = {{convert|986|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref>https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/caribische-deel-van-het-koninkrijk/vraag-en-antwoord/waaruit-bestaat-het-koninkrijk-der-nederlanden</ref>\n| label2    = Population<br/>{{small|(as of January 2019)}}\n| data2     = 337,617<ref>https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/caribische-deel-van-het-koninkrijk/vraag-en-antwoord/waaruit-bestaat-het-koninkrijk-der-nederlanden</ref>\n| label3    = GDP (Nominal)\n| data3     = US$ 8.911 billion<ref name=\"CIA GDP\">[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/cc.html COUNTRY COMPARISON GDP] {{Webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5tg9oCW4Y?url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/cc.html |date=2010-10-22 }}, [[Central Intelligence Agency]].</ref>\n| label4    = GDP per Capita (Nominal)\n| data4     = US$ 29,240<ref name=\"CIA GDP\">[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/cc.html COUNTRY COMPARISON GDP] {{Webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/5tg9oCW4Y?url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/cc.html |date=2010-10-22 }}, [[Central Intelligence Agency]].</ref>\n| label5    = [[Population density|Density]]\n| data5     = {{convert|343|/km2|abbr=on}}\n| label6    = Languages\n| data6     = [[Dutch language|Dutch]], [[English language|English]], [[Papiamento]]\n| label7    = Government\n| data7     = 3 [[Kingdom of the Netherlands#Constituent countries|constituent countries]]<br />3 [[Caribbean Netherlands#Administration|special municipalities]]\n}}\n\nThe '''Dutch Caribbean''' (historically known as the '''Dutch West Indies''') are the territories, colonies, and countries, both former and current, of the [[Dutch Empire]] and the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]] that are located in the [[Lesser Antilles]] archipelago of the [[Caribbean Sea]]. \n\nCurrently the Dutch Caribbean consists of the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands#Constituent countries|constituent countries]] of [[Aruba]], [[Cura\u00e7ao]] and [[Sint Maarten]]; and the [[Caribbean Netherlands#Administration|special municipalities]] of [[Bonaire]], [[Sint Eustatius]] and [[Saba]].<ref>https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/caribische-deel-van-het-koninkrijk/vraag-en-antwoord/waaruit-bestaat-het-koninkrijk-der-nederlanden</ref> The contemporary term is sometimes also used for the [[Caribbean Netherlands]], an entity consisting of the three special municipalities forming part of the constituent country of the [[Netherlands]] since 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rijksdienstcn.com/en?1curvers=engels&0Lang=E|title=Rijksdienst Carbische Nederland (Rijksdienst Dutch Caribbean)|accessdate=4 June 2015|work=Government of the Netherlands|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702121227/http://www.rijksdienstcn.com/en?1curvers=engels&0Lang=E|archive-date=2 July 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Visa for the Dutch Caribbean|url=http://unitedkingdom.nlembassy.org/passports-visas--consular/visas/visa-for-the-dutch-caribbean.html|publisher=Netherlands Embassy in the United Kingdom|accessdate=4 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140119043938/http://unitedkingdom.nlembassy.org/passports-visas--consular/visas/visa-for-the-dutch-caribbean.html|archive-date=19 January 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The Dutch Caribbean has a population of 337,617 as of January 2019.<ref>https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/caribische-deel-van-het-koninkrijk/vraag-en-antwoord/waaruit-bestaat-het-koninkrijk-der-nederlanden</ref>\n\n==History==\n{{further|Dutch colonization of the Americas|Dutch West India Company}}\nThe islands in the Dutch Caribbean were from 1815 on part of the colonies  [[Cura\u00e7ao and Dependencies]] (1815\u20131828) or [[Sint Eustatius and Dependencies]] (1815-1828), which were merged with [[Surinam (Dutch colony)|colony of Suriname]] (not considered part of the Dutch Caribbean, although it was on the southern Caribbean in Northeastern [[South America]]) and governed from Paramaribo until 1845, when all islands became part of the colony again called Cura\u00e7ao and Dependencies.\n\nIn 1954, the islands became the [[Countries of the Kingdom of the Netherlands|country]] (Dutch: ''Land'') [[Netherlands Antilles]] (1954\u22122010). The autonomy of the Netherlands Antilles' island territories was specified in the [[Islands Regulation of the Netherlands Antilles]]. Initially the Netherlands Antilles consisted of 4 island territories: Aruba, Bonaire, Cura\u00e7ao and the Windward Islands. The latter split into the Island Territories Saba, Sint Eustatius and Sint Maarten in 1983.\n\nThe island of Aruba seceded from the Netherlands Antilles in 1986 to become a separate constituent country of the [[Kingdom of the Netherlands]], leaving five island territories within the Netherlands Antilles. This situation remained until the complete [[dissolution of the Netherlands Antilles]] as a unified political entity in 2010. In that year Cura\u00e7ao and Sint Maarten became autonomous constituent countries within the Kingdom (like Aruba); while Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba became [[Caribbean Netherlands|special municipalities]] of the [[Netherlands]] proper, which is the constituent country that is mainly located in Europe.\n\n==Geography==\nCurrently, there are two main divisions in the Dutch Caribbean:\n* those islands that have the status of being constituent countries of the Kingdom of the Netherlands\n* those islands that have the status of being special municipalities of the Netherlands alone, as distinct from the Kingdom in its entirety.\n\n===Constituent countries===\n[[File:Punda otrabanda.jpg|thumb|[[Willemstad]], the capital of [[Cura\u00e7ao]] and the largest city in the Dutch Caribbean]]\n[[File:Stan Patrol P810 Jaguar Dutch Caribbean Coastguard.jpg|thumb|[[Dutch Caribbean Coast Guard]] cutter]]\nThere are three Caribbean islands that are countries ({{lang-nl|landen}}) within the Kingdom of the Netherlands: [[Aruba]], [[Cura\u00e7ao]], and [[Sint Maarten]]. The [[Netherlands]] is the fourth and largest constituent country in the Kingdom.\n\nSint Maarten comprises approximately one half of the island of [[Saint Martin]]. The northern half of the island \u2013 the [[Collectivity of Saint Martin]] \u2013 is an overseas territory of [[France]].\n\n===Special municipalities===\n{{Main|Caribbean Netherlands}}\nThe three Caribbean islands that are [[Public body (Netherlands)|special municipalities]] of the Netherlands alone are [[Bonaire]], [[Sint Eustatius]], and [[Saba]]. Collectively, these special municipalities of the Netherlands are also known as the \"[[BES islands]]\" or the [[Caribbean Netherlands]].\n\n==Comparison==\n{| style=\"background:none;\" cellspacing=\"2\"\n|\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:40px;\" class=\"unsortable\"| Flag\n! style=\"width:110px;\"| Name\n! style=\"width:120px;\"| Capital\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Area<ref>https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/caribische-deel-van-het-koninkrijk/vraag-en-antwoord/waaruit-bestaat-het-koninkrijk-der-nederlanden</ref>\n! style=\"width:90px;\"| Population<ref>https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/caribische-deel-van-het-koninkrijk/vraag-en-antwoord/waaruit-bestaat-het-koninkrijk-der-nederlanden</ref><br />(January 2019)\n! style=\"width:80px;\"|Density\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|{{flagicon|Aruba|size=27px}} || [[Aruba]] || <center>[[Oranjestad, Aruba]]</center> || style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|180|km2|sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}|| style=\"text-align:right\"|112,309|| style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|624|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|{{flagicon|Bonaire|size=27px}} || [[Bonaire]] || <center>[[Kralendijk]]</center> || style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|294|km2|sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}|| style=\"text-align:right\"|20,104|| style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|69|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|{{flagicon|Cura\u00e7ao|size=27px}} || [[Cura\u00e7ao]] || <center>[[Willemstad]]</center> || style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|444|km2|sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}|| style=\"text-align:right\"|158,665|| style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|358|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|{{flagicon|Saba|size=27px}} || [[Saba]] || <center>[[The Bottom]]</center> || style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|13|km2|sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}|| style=\"text-align:right\"|1,915|| style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|148|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|{{flagicon|Sint Eustatius|size=27px}} || [[Sint Eustatius]] || <center>[[Oranjestad, Sint Eustatius]]</center> || style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|21|km2|sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}|| style=\"text-align:right\"|3,138|| style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|150|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center\"|{{flagicon|Sint Maarten|size=27px}} || [[Sint Maarten]] || <center>[[Philipsburg, Sint Maarten|Philipsburg]]</center> || style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|34|km2|sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}|| style=\"text-align:right\"|41,486|| style=\"text-align:right\"|{{convert|1221|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:right;\"| Total\n! style=\"text-align:right;\"| {{convert|986|km2|sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n! style=\"text-align:right;\"| 337,617\n! style=\"text-align:right;\"| {{convert|343|/km2|/sqmi|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|}\n|}\n\n==Grouping of islands==\nThe islands have also been informally grouped in the following ways:\n* [[ABC islands (Lesser Antilles)|ABC islands]], for [[Aruba]], [[Bonaire]], and [[Cura\u00e7ao]] (clustered in the [[Leeward Antilles]] group);\n* [[SSS islands]], for [[Saba]], [[Sint Eustatius]], and [[Sint Maarten]] (clustered in the [[Leeward Islands]] group);\n* [[BES islands]],<ref name=\"bes-acs\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rvo.nl/subsidies-regelingen/partners-international-business-pib |title=Partners for International Business (PIB) |language=Dutch |work=Dutch Government |accessdate=20 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625161327/https://www.rvo.nl/subsidies-regelingen/partners-international-business-pib |archive-date=25 June 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> for Bonaire, Sint Eustatius, and Saba (also known as the Caribbean Netherlands);\n* [[ACS islands]],<ref name=\"bes-acs\" /> for Aruba, Cura\u00e7ao and Sint Maarten (the islands outside the Caribbean Netherlands).\n\n<gallery widths=\"300px\" heights=\"200px\">\nDutch Caribbean map.png|Map of the Dutch Caribbean islands.\nKingdom of the Netherlands location tree.svg|Those countries and special municipalities of the Kingdom of the Netherlands that are located in the Caribbean (blue background) form the Dutch Caribbean.\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Dutch navy in the Caribbean]]\n*[[Cura\u00e7aoans in the Netherlands]]\n*[[Arubans in the Netherlands]]\n*[[Dutch West Indian Americans]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{